I have the same issue. I can't use my VMs, at all. Every time I run virt-manager, open the window for my (already running) VM, and click inside, virt-manager crashes.

Proposing as a Beta blocker: "The release must be able host virtual guest instances of the same release. ...when using Fedora's recommended virtualization technology, that is. This criterion applies only to the recommended Fedora virtualization tools - the qemu/kvm - libvirt - virt-manager stack." https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_25_Beta_Release_Criteria#Self_hosting_virtualization
virt-viewer crashes as well, but abrt didn't allow me to create a report. Seems to be the same issue.

This is the update that breaks virt-manager:
Command Line : distro-sync gtk3* Transaction performed with: Installed dnf-1.1.10-1.fc25.noarch @@commandline Installed rpm-4.13.0-0.rc1.46.fc25.x86_64 @@commandline Packages Altered: Upgraded gtk3-3.21.4-2.fc25.x86_64 @fedora Upgrade 3.21.5-1.fc25.x86_64 @updates-testing Upgraded gtk3-devel-3.21.4-2.fc25.x86_64 @fedora Upgrade 3.21.5-1.fc25.x86_64 @updates-testing
So this is technically not a blocker if the package is not pushed stable.
https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=770952 should fix this

(In reply to Kamil Páral from comment #13) > I have the same issue. I can't use my VMs, at all. Every time I run > virt-manager, open the window for my (already running) VM, and click inside, > virt-manager crashes.
To clarify the reproducer, the crash occurs when you click into a VM which is in graphical mode (tested with GNOME). If you click inside a VM which is in text mode, the crash doesn't occur.
*** Bug 1373668 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
The same issue seems to occur in libreoffice, see bug 1373668.
After further debugging this turned out to be a mutter issue. Should be fixed in mutter-3.21.91-2.fc25
